@node MAIN_WINDOW "Color-Riddle/Playing/Main-Window"
When the program starts, the main-window appears.

The highscore-list is shown at the bottom of the window. If you leave the program, it is saved automatically.

You can leave the program only from the main-window. To do so you have either to click on the closewindow-gagdet in the left top edge or to press the escape-key.


@{u}Gadgets@{uu}

@{b}Mode@{ub} (Keys: 1-5)
With these radio-gadgets, you can choose the current gamemode.
At the right side the attributes of the current gamemode are displayed.

@{b}@{u}C@{uu}hange@{ub}
The current mode can be changed with this gadget (Oh yes :-)). (see @{"Settings" link MODES_WINDOW}).

@{b}@{u}P@{uu}layer@{ub}
With this cycle-gadget you can choose the number of players (1-4). Every game is repeated as many times as the gadget "Player" shows.

@{b}@{u}T@{uu}able@{ub}
You can open the @{"table" link TABLE} with this gadget. (Unbelivable!)

@{b}@{u}S@{uu}tart@{ub}
At last you can start the @{"game" link GAME} with this gadget.


@{u}Menu@{uu}

@{b}@{u}S@{uu}ame game@{ub}
This submenu repeats the last game.

@{b}@{u}H@{uu}elp@{ub}
Guess!

@{b}About@{ub} (@{u}?@{uu})
This submenu shows an informationrequester.

@{b}@{u}I@{uu}conize@{ub}
If you choose this submenu, the window and the screen close and an icon is drawn on the workbench. If you double-click on this icon, the screen and the window open again.

@{b}@{u}C@{uu}hoose screenmode@{ub}
You can choose the screenmode with this menu. It opens a standard ASL-requester. Therefore it is only availble with asl.library V38 or higher!

@{b}Show @{u}n@{uu}umbers@{ub}
If this submenu is activated, not only colors but also numbers are shown.

@{b}Sa@{u}v@{uu}e settings@{ub}
With this submenu you can save the settings (current game, show numbers, screenmode and autoscroll) to the tooltypes of Color-Riddle.info.
@endnode


@node MODES_WINDOW "Color-Riddle/Playing/Settings"
@{u}Gadgets@{uu}

@{b}@{u}N@{uu}ame@{ub}
With this gadget you can choose a name for the current gamemode. You can use up to 20 characters.

@{b}@{u}C@{uu}olors@{ub}
With this slider you can choose how many colors you want to use. (4-8)

@{b}@{u}D@{uu}ouble colors@{ub}
If this checkbox isn't activated you can't use a color more than once. 
@{b}Important@{ub}: It is not possible that "@Double colors" is deactivated and at the same time you have less colors than fields.

@{b}@{u}F@{uu}ields@{ub}
With this slider you can choose the number of fields you are allowed to use. (2-8)

@{b}{u}R@{uu}ounds@{ub}
With this slider you can choose the number of rounds you are allowed to use. (2-20)

@{b}@{u}S@{uu}ave@{ub}
With this gadget you can save the gamemodes.
@{b}Important@{ub}: Not only the current mode is saved but all modes!

@{b}@{u}U@{uu}se@{ub}
With this gadget you can use a mode without saving. But if you save another mode later this mode is saved too!

@{b}@{u}C@{uu}ancel@{ub}
With this gadget you can reset the current gamemode. If you click on the closewindow-gadget or press the escape key the same happens.

If you use the gadgets "@{u}S@{uu}ave", "@{u}U@{uu}se" or "@{u}C@{uu}ancel" the @{"Main-Window" link MAIN_WINDOW} opens again.


@{u}Menu@{uu}

@{b}@{u}H@{uu}elp@{ub}
Guess!

@{b}@{u}I@{uu}conize@{ub}
If you choose this submenu, the window and the screen close and an icon is drawn on the workbench. If you double-click on this icon, the screen and the window open again.
@endnode



