@node GAME "Color-Riddle/Playing/Game"
Before every game, a requester shows the current player.

@{u}Choosing the color@{uu}
With the palette-gadget or the F-Keys you can choose the current color. 
@{b}Note:@{ub} With WB 2.1 (V38) or lower the palette-gadget could contain more colors than usable!

@{u}Setting the fields@{uu}
To set the fields with the current color you have to click on the gadgets in the current column or to press one of the keys 1-8.

@{u}Confirming the color@{uu}
You can check the current column with the gadget "@{u}O@{uu}K" or the Enter-key. The result is drawn as black and white lines below the current column.
If you found out the right combination and if you earned enough points, the @{"highscore-window" link HIGHSCORES} opens.
After that the either next player can play or the @{"main-window" link MAIN_WINDOW} opens again.
But if it was the last column no highscore-window opens :-)
Else the next row is pre-filled. If nothing happens, you used a color more than once although "@{u}D@{uu}ouble colors" was disabled!

@{u}Quitting the game@{uu}
The current game can be canceled by clicking the closewindow-gadget or
pressing the escape-key.


@{u}Menu@{uu}

@{b}@{u}R@{uu}edraw@{ub}
Redraws all the fields.

@{b}@{u}H@{uu}elp@{ub}
Guess!

@{b}@{u}I@{uu}conize@{ub}
If you choose this submenu, the window and the screen close and an icon is drawn on the workbench. If you double-click on this icon, the screen and the window open again.
@endnode


@node HIGHSCORES "Color-Riddle/Using/Highscores"
